				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I've heard of both using the audio buffer for frame throttling as a solution as well as adjusting the actual number of samples generated for the buffer to better match VSYNC. I think the actual NES runs slightly faster than 60hz which causes a problem if you generate the correct number of samples and sync the emulator with 60hz vsync. It depends on how you generate your audio but you may be able to do the adjustment when generating your audio data to make sure the number of total samples is equal to how many you need for each video frame.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

