						<div class="postbody">Bizhawk has a throttle to audio mode, where you block in the audio thread if there's not enough room for all of the samples, and a wizard mode, where various black magics are used to attempt to stretch\squeeze audio without sounding horrid.  (To be used with other throttles like clock-based or vsync-based).<br /><br />Honestly, the whole thing is horrible and you'll never please everyone, even if your emulator is bristling with options.</div>

